main event: A witness observed a bright, red or orange object in the sky near Eugene, Oregon on July 25, 1966.
interesting points: The object was visible for 15-20 seconds and appeared to be quite far away from the witness.
The witness said the object was brighter than the brightest stars.
The object drifted behind some tall trees and was obscured, then later passed in front of the trees.
The witness estimated the angular size of the object to be about 5 using a match stick at arm's length.
The witness drew a sketch showing a round, featureless object.
result: Likely an aircraft, based on the description provided.
sighted object: a bright, red or orange object
